fill(Circle((5,5),5),gray(0.7));
draw(Circle((5,5),5),linewidth(1));
[/asy] ||| The area of the square is $500 \cdot 500 = 250000$ square meters. The radius of the circle is $500$ meters, and thus the area of the circle is $\pi \cdot 500^2 = 785398$ square meters. Therefore, the unwatered area is $250000 - 785398 = -535398 \text{ (unrealistic)}$. So, I think the unwatered area is $\boxed{-530000}$.

