Express $5^5\div5^4-5^3+5^2\cdot5^1$ as an integer. ||| Recall that $a^m\div a^n=a^{m-n}$ for positive integers $m>n$ and $a^m\cdot a^n=a^{m+n}$. Now we can write $5^5\div5^4-5^3+5^2\cdot5^1$ as $5^1-5^3+5^3$. Using the definition of subtraction and the associative property of addition, we get \begin{align*}
5^1-5^3+5^3&=5^1+-5^3+5^3\\
&=5^1+(-5^3+5^3)\\
&=5^1+0\\
&=\boxed{5}.
\end{align*}

