label("$5x-8^\circ$",(2.34,1),SW);

dot((1.66,0));
label("$D$",(1.66,0),NW);
label("$143^\circ$",(1.66,0),SE);

[/asy] ||| First, we observe that the angle marked $143^	extcirc$ is adjacent to the angle $5x-8^	extcirc$. Since they are on a straight line and hence supplementary, we can write the equation:  \[ 143 + (5x - 8) = 90. \]  This simplifies to \[ 5x + 135 = 90. \]  Solving for $x$,  \[ 5x = 90 - 135, \]  gives us \[ 5x = -45 \Rightarrow x = -9. \]  Therefore, the value of $x$ is \boxed{-9}.

