In triangle $PQR$, point $T$ is on $PR$ and point $S$ is on $PQ$ such that $TS \parallel RQ$. The measure of $\angle RPQ$ is $65^{\circ}$, and the measure of $\angle TSQ$ is $145^{\circ}$. What is the measure of $\angle PRQ$? ||| [asy]
